	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div><i>Linking the stats of some uber robe in serverwise.graffe kinda kills the mystique of the item as far as I'm concerned</i><br />
<br />
I disagree, I see item linking as keeping the mystique.  You don't have to click on it.  Someone typing the stats out flat into serverwide.graffe, however, will completely eliminate any mystique.<br />
<br />
It's also kind of cool to see items passed around that I probably would never have ever heard of otherwise.<br />
<br />
<br />
<i>If recognizing items up close is not such a chore in a new game, there will be no need for cheesy item links.</i><br />
<br />
Granted, I would like to see much more identifiable characteristics in worn items on the model, but this is not always feasable, and substantially increases the asset cost of developing content.<br />
<br />
In fact, I think that right clicking on someone should show the stats of an item.  I never understood why you only ever saw the name, then inevitably had to ask someone to &quot;put it in a trade window&quot; or &quot;type up the stats&quot;.  <br />
